1
00:00:05,733 --> 00:00:07,973
(Previously) Is it exhausting
hanging out with my family?

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,000
It's fun, actually.

3
00:00:15,066 --> 00:00:16,066
Damn it, Erng.

4
00:00:22,166 --> 00:00:23,166
Hia.

5
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:28,600
Get out.

6
00:00:30,733 --> 00:00:32,373
And don't you ever
set foot in here again.

7
00:00:51,057 --> 00:00:52,424
Don't ever
go back to him.

8
00:00:54,533 --> 00:00:55,933
Go get your wounds treated first.

9
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:01,080
Hia, can you please not be like this?

10
00:01:16,133 --> 00:01:17,300
Go take a shower.

11
00:01:18,166 --> 00:01:19,166
I'll wait for you here.

12
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:20,700
In-In.

13
00:01:21,666 --> 00:01:23,133
We could shower together, you know.

14
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,866
I know this kind of
thing will happen again.

15
00:01:35,533 --> 00:01:37,733
Bom might come back and bother us again.

16
00:01:40,366 --> 00:01:41,866
Would it be selfish of me?

17
00:01:42,700 --> 00:01:45,166
If I asked you to be
patient and stay with me?

18
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,866
This might sound a bit dramatic.

19
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:55,933
But I really, really like you, Hia.

20
00:01:57,566 --> 00:01:59,066
You make me feel important.

21
00:01:59,866 --> 00:02:00,866
Special.

22
00:02:01,933 --> 00:02:04,166
You're not afraid to tell
people you're into me.

23
00:02:05,533 --> 00:02:07,933
I feel so incredibly lucky to have met you.

24
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:13,266
But everything is moving too fast.

25
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:17,400
Too fast for me to be sure
that I won't get left behind again.

26
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,300
I can trust you, right?

27
00:02:29,766 --> 00:02:31,166
If you're having second thoughts...

28
00:02:32,533 --> 00:02:33,866
You're missing out, Erng.

29
00:02:37,666 --> 00:02:42,300
Let me tell you, you'll never find anyone
who treats you as well as I do.

30
00:02:48,533 --> 00:02:50,373
A minute ago, you asked
me to shower with you.

31
00:02:53,766 --> 00:02:55,066
Such a good memory.

32
00:02:59,666 --> 00:03:02,186
I remember I was going to have
my way with Erng-Erng ten times.

33
00:03:14,066 --> 00:03:15,533
My little one.

34
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:49,000
"ChermChey"
(Episode 4)

35
00:05:12,378 --> 00:05:13,878
You look like a wet puppy.

36
00:05:15,333 --> 00:05:17,533
Can't you be romantic
for just five minutes?

37
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:18,900
Huh?

38
00:05:21,066 --> 00:05:23,515
You're one to talk, with your big ears.

39
00:05:23,516 --> 00:05:24,815
And your dark butt.

40
00:05:25,464 --> 00:05:27,176
And no one says a thing.

41
00:05:27,177 --> 00:05:28,457
A little harsh, don't you think?

42
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,000
Now I'm sulking.

43
00:05:36,913 --> 00:05:38,384
Come on… don't be mad.

44
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:41,847
Big ears and dark butt, but
you're still Erng-Erng's boyfriend.

45
00:05:41,848 --> 00:05:43,848
There, there.

46
00:05:46,366 --> 00:05:48,046
Hey, I'm done trying to make it up to you.

47
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:55,400
Fine, I'm over it.

48
00:06:02,166 --> 00:06:03,311
What?

49
00:06:05,165 --> 00:06:06,165
I don't get it.

50
00:06:10,747 --> 00:06:12,382
Intha, what's wrong with you?

51
00:06:14,654 --> 00:06:15,654
Can I?

52
00:06:16,574 --> 00:06:17,574
What?

53
00:06:18,569 --> 00:06:19,569
Please?

54
00:06:19,779 --> 00:06:20,568
What?

55
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,101
In, if you don't say it...

56
00:06:22,286 --> 00:06:23,776
How am I supposed to understand?

57
00:06:29,566 --> 00:06:31,721
If you don't tell me, I won't know.

58
00:06:33,263 --> 00:06:34,263
I can't say it.

59
00:06:34,527 --> 00:06:35,564
It's like...

60
00:06:37,743 --> 00:06:39,212
Ow, ow! That hurts!

61
00:06:39,677 --> 00:06:41,241
Please? Can I have it?

62
00:06:43,606 --> 00:06:44,952
Please?

63
00:06:53,391 --> 00:06:55,102
How dare you?

64
00:06:55,103 --> 00:06:56,103
Come on.

65
00:06:57,075 --> 00:06:58,148
Get out of there.

66
00:06:58,380 --> 00:07:00,000
Still not done brushing your teeth?

67
00:07:34,766 --> 00:07:35,866
Hia, what are you doing?

68
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:49,500
Hey!

69
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:52,466
Why did you draw such a funny face on me?

70
00:08:10,666 --> 00:08:12,500
I was trying my best, you know.

71
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:19,400
Here, let me help.

72
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:45,966
I'm the luckiest guy in the world.

73
00:08:48,133 --> 00:08:49,133
For what?

74
00:08:51,466 --> 00:08:53,666
Lucky to have you as my
wifey, right here with me.

75
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:08,166
And do you think I'm lucky?

76
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:30,766
I'm very lucky.

77
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:33,400
Even luckier than you are.

78
00:10:29,452 --> 00:10:32,460
Is Erng-Erng awake yet?

79
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:10,423
A ghost!

80
00:11:10,424 --> 00:11:11,935
It's me.

81
00:11:11,936 --> 00:11:13,444
What's your problem?

82
00:11:14,696 --> 00:11:17,284
Hia, a ghost just scared me.

83
00:11:18,026 --> 00:11:20,000
A ghost? So I'm a ghost now?

84
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,000
Take it easy.

85
00:11:27,733 --> 00:11:29,100
Go take a shower now.

86
00:11:30,166 --> 00:11:32,006
Don't we have a meeting
to review the designs?

87
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:33,300
Ugh.

88
00:11:33,466 --> 00:11:34,800
I'm still scared of the ghost.

89
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:38,766
Go take a shower.

90
00:11:39,266 --> 00:11:41,791
You scared the life out of me, Hia.

91
00:11:41,792 --> 00:11:43,566
I think I'll just rest a little longer.

92
00:11:44,766 --> 00:11:45,766
Go take a shower.

93
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:48,934
I'm scared of ghosts.

94
00:11:49,490 --> 00:11:51,757
I think I'll just go back to sleep.

95
00:11:53,704 --> 00:11:55,455
Time to take a shower.

96
00:11:56,104 --> 00:11:57,109
Let's go.

97
00:11:57,387 --> 00:11:58,507
I said no.

98
00:12:01,898 --> 00:12:02,971
I said I'm not going.

99
00:12:03,250 --> 00:12:03,928
Get down.

100
00:12:04,207 --> 00:12:05,207
Get down here.

101
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:10,652
Hia!

102
00:12:11,023 --> 00:12:12,023
Go.

103
00:12:13,248 --> 00:12:14,248
Hia!

104
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,179
Hurry up and shower. It's getting late.

105
00:12:17,180 --> 00:12:19,540
How dare you treat the
princess of this industry like this?

106
00:12:19,648 --> 00:12:20,728
The amulet industry, maybe?

107
00:12:21,005 --> 00:12:22,040
Hurry up.

108
00:12:22,921 --> 00:12:24,064
If you don't let go...

109
00:12:24,333 --> 00:12:26,000
You sleep at your own place tonight.

110
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:36,700
Are you sore?

111
00:12:38,866 --> 00:12:39,906
Let me give you a massage.

112
00:12:41,133 --> 00:12:43,360
Massage, massage, and more massage.

113
00:12:45,029 --> 00:12:47,134
You must be really sore.

114
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:51,700
Sore, huh?

115
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:54,300
So tense.

116
00:12:54,766 --> 00:12:57,400
Tense enough to kick
someone around here, I bet.

117
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:59,566
That should relieve the pain for a while.

118
00:12:59,700 --> 00:13:01,066
There's no one here to kick.

119
00:13:04,166 --> 00:13:05,166
You're really tense here.

120
00:13:06,937 --> 00:13:08,400
Ooh, a twitching muscle.

121
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:10,200
Just a little more.

122
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:14,500
Oh, never mind.

123
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:22,300
Erng.

124
00:13:23,666 --> 00:13:24,666
Um...

125
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:28,500
What's today's lucky color?

126
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:36,466
Is it black, maybe?

127
00:13:38,266 --> 00:13:41,300
I wonder if Erng-Erng
has washed his black outfit.

128
00:13:43,533 --> 00:13:47,200
If not, what will you wear?

129
00:13:54,466 --> 00:13:55,466
I mean...

130
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:58,000
You can wear mine.

131
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:00,600
Here.

132
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:09,884
Wow, cool, right?

133
00:14:09,885 --> 00:14:13,466
Just like mine.
Wear this and it will be lucky day.

134
00:14:19,266 --> 00:14:20,946
Seems like we're not going anywhere today.

135
00:14:22,366 --> 00:14:23,366
Cute, huh?

136
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:27,500
So you'll wear this today, okay?

137
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:33,300
Just kill me.

138
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:39,760
If you wanted us to wear matching
shirts, you should've just said so.

139
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,476
I don't know what you're talking about.

140
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:43,466
Leave the shirt over there.

141
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:46,133
Here?

142
00:14:46,134 --> 00:14:47,200
Yup!

143
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:48,500
I'm going to shower now.

144
00:14:49,166 --> 00:14:50,166
Whoa.

145
00:15:04,666 --> 00:15:06,566
Erng, I'll come help you change your shirt.

146
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,466
This is the latest design.

147
00:15:27,166 --> 00:15:30,333
Oh, Hia, which do you
prefer? This one or this one?

148
00:15:34,066 --> 00:15:35,266
I like the leather ones.

149
00:15:36,366 --> 00:15:37,366
But...

150
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:40,066
I don't think it matches the shop's vibe.

151
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:41,680
That's what I was thinking.

152
00:15:42,966 --> 00:15:44,133
Let's go with this one, then.

153
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,280
Is there anything else you want to change?

154
00:15:46,866 --> 00:15:47,866
Hmm.

155
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:54,765
Please take your time, Mr. Erng and Mr. In.
I'm just going to use the restroom.

156
00:15:54,766 --> 00:15:55,566
Okay.

157
00:15:55,566 --> 00:15:56,566
Sure.

158
00:16:08,666 --> 00:16:09,966
Your shirt's untucked.

159
00:16:10,866 --> 00:16:12,300
Tuck it in like this.

160
00:16:12,566 --> 00:16:13,566
Like I did.

161
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:15,400
No way.

162
00:16:16,066 --> 00:16:17,706
It feels uncomfortable when I tuck it in.

163
00:16:21,826 --> 00:16:23,466
That's because you're not doing it right.

164
00:16:31,866 --> 00:16:32,866
Let me help.

165
00:16:39,266 --> 00:16:40,900
I'm helping you tuck it in.

166
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:44,133
I don't need help. I can do it myself.

167
00:16:54,166 --> 00:16:55,246
So, what do you guys think?

168
00:16:55,959 --> 00:16:57,959
Just let me know if you
want any adjustments.

169
00:16:58,466 --> 00:16:59,466
Got it.

170
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:26,300
I'm not eating it.

171
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,000
Hmph.

172
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:30,933
But I ordered this for you.

173
00:17:32,366 --> 00:17:33,400
I don't eat sweets.

174
00:17:38,066 --> 00:17:39,066
Alright then.

175
00:18:06,533 --> 00:18:08,053
Excuse me, I need to use the restroom.

176
00:18:08,566 --> 00:18:09,566
Sure.

177
00:18:17,733 --> 00:18:18,733
Excuse me.

178
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,200
Okay.

179
00:18:29,666 --> 00:18:30,666
We're here.

180
00:18:31,600 --> 00:18:33,300
My friends should all be here by now.

181
00:18:34,166 --> 00:18:35,166
Which place is it?

182
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:36,300
Just follow me.

183
00:18:36,466 --> 00:18:37,866
You'll find out soon, little Erng.

184
00:18:41,273 --> 00:18:43,473
Are we really going to walk
in holding hands like this?

185
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,000
Feeling awkward?

186
00:18:48,300 --> 00:18:50,566
If you're too shy, you can let go.

187
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:54,933
Uh, it's not that I'm shy or anything.

188
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:00,900
This place?

189
00:19:02,966 --> 00:19:03,966
Uh-huh.

190
00:19:04,333 --> 00:19:06,300
My friends are obsessed with the food here.

191
00:19:06,900 --> 00:19:09,109
Every time they're back in
Thailand, they have to eat here.

192
00:19:09,133 --> 00:19:11,500
They say you can't find
anything like it abroad.

193
00:19:12,666 --> 00:19:13,466
This is it.

194
00:19:13,666 --> 00:19:14,733
Our go-to spot.

195
00:19:15,533 --> 00:19:16,533
It's nice.

196
00:19:16,866 --> 00:19:18,626
The menu looks like
it has a lot of variety.

197
00:19:19,766 --> 00:19:21,086
And the atmosphere is great, too.

198
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:32,400
Hey, In's here!

199
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:33,700
Hey, what's up?

200
00:19:34,333 --> 00:19:35,333
Hey, everyone.

201
00:19:40,766 --> 00:19:42,900
Sit down. We saved a spot for you.

202
00:19:45,133 --> 00:19:46,133
Bro.

203
00:19:46,366 --> 00:19:47,500
I'm going to sit over there.

204
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:48,789
I like the rough-and-tumble type of guy.

205
00:19:48,790 --> 00:19:49,790
Erng.

206
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:55,100
Hello.

207
00:19:59,966 --> 00:20:00,966
Yours.

208
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:15,300
Sit down.

209
00:20:15,366 --> 00:20:17,500
Are you going to
circle the table all night?

210
00:20:18,566 --> 00:20:19,566
Sit.

211
00:20:27,733 --> 00:20:29,166
What happened to your face?

212
00:20:31,333 --> 00:20:33,866
Did you mess with some
gangster's wife and get beaten up?

213
00:20:34,100 --> 00:20:34,619
Huh?

214
00:20:34,619 --> 00:20:35,619
My wife beat me up.

215
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,200
Really, Hia?

216
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:41,500
Wait, wait, wait.

217
00:20:42,266 --> 00:20:43,266
You.

218
00:20:43,533 --> 00:20:44,566
You have a wife?

219
00:20:44,766 --> 00:20:46,200
Another tough one, huh?

220
00:20:46,666 --> 00:20:49,306
Did you try to find your inner
peace while she was wailing on you?

221
00:20:51,366 --> 00:20:54,966
Just take everything he
says with a grain of salt.

222
00:20:58,533 --> 00:20:59,533
Yeah, so what?

223
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:02,333
Is that Erng?

224
00:21:03,766 --> 00:21:06,533
Yeah, that's Erng. This is Nai.

225
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:10,300
Hello.

226
00:21:11,066 --> 00:21:12,300
And what about Rit?

227
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:13,800
He's working.

228
00:21:13,933 --> 00:21:15,013
But he'll pick me up later.

229
00:21:17,266 --> 00:21:18,909
And the handsome guy sitting over there...

230
00:21:18,933 --> 00:21:19,933
is Mr. Aiyaret.

231
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:23,061
My young millionaire. That's him.

232
00:21:23,062 --> 00:21:25,489
And the one stuffing
his face with chicken...

233
00:21:26,277 --> 00:21:27,277
is Chen-Nai.

234
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:30,494
They're a couple.

235
00:21:30,911 --> 00:21:35,668
He's not worth a hundred million, but from the
way he eats, he probably weighs a hundred kilos.

236
00:21:36,734 --> 00:21:38,269
You bastard.

237
00:21:39,613 --> 00:21:41,116
Hello.

238
00:21:48,733 --> 00:21:51,126
You look familiar. Are you famous?

239
00:21:52,424 --> 00:21:53,717
My name is Chon.

240
00:21:54,166 --> 00:21:55,166
Chonlatee.

241
00:21:56,100 --> 00:21:57,300
This is Chonlatee.

242
00:21:59,533 --> 00:22:00,333
Hello.

243
00:22:00,334 --> 00:22:01,366
Hello.

244
00:22:02,366 --> 00:22:03,966
He's Ton's boyfriend.

245
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:07,300
Hello.

246
00:22:07,466 --> 00:22:08,466
Hello.

247
00:22:16,666 --> 00:22:18,666
So much love in the air.

248
00:22:20,166 --> 00:22:22,066
P'Chon, I'm sorry.

249
00:22:22,766 --> 00:22:24,366
You look so familiar to me.

250
00:22:24,733 --> 00:22:27,933
Are you a YouTuber
or do you have a travel page or something?

251
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:30,533
The one who takes
the unicorn doll on trips?

252
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:34,300
Um, I do have a channel, but...

253
00:22:37,966 --> 00:22:39,666
I don't really have time to post videos.

254
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:43,133
It depends on when
P'Ton is free to take me out.

255
00:22:43,733 --> 00:22:44,733
I've seen it.

256
00:22:45,166 --> 00:22:47,333
I love that unicorn doll so much.

257
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:51,266
But in person, you're so cute, Chon.

258
00:22:58,300 --> 00:22:59,300
Ow!

259
00:22:59,366 --> 00:23:00,166
In!

260
00:23:00,266 --> 00:23:01,700
Why did you step on my shoe?

261
00:23:02,066 --> 00:23:03,066
It's expensive, man!

262
00:23:05,133 --> 00:23:06,866
Why did you step on his foot?

263
00:23:07,366 --> 00:23:09,866
Yeah, I'm confused. Why'd you step on me?

264
00:23:10,100 --> 00:23:10,966
I was trying to step on Erng.

265
00:23:10,966 --> 00:23:11,466
Oh.

266
00:23:11,566 --> 00:23:12,566
Why would you step on me?

267
00:23:13,066 --> 00:23:14,066
I was jealous.

268
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:20,634
Come on, Erng, switch seats with me.

269
00:23:21,468 --> 00:23:23,642
Sorry, my dear buddy monk.

270
00:23:23,643 --> 00:23:26,820
I didn't know you two were a thing.

271
00:23:27,608 --> 00:23:30,388
If I knew, I would have...

272
00:23:34,900 --> 00:23:36,300
Yeah, great.

273
00:23:36,500 --> 00:23:37,800
Everyone has a boyfriend.

274
00:23:38,466 --> 00:23:39,666
Whoever doesn't have one...

275
00:23:39,866 --> 00:23:41,366
can just get out of the gang.

276
